      "uuid": "8686cec711844987a0f1038edabb2edf",
      "x": 13579.692885815102,
      "y": 3369.6743969436316,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 161.0,
      "z_value": -9.91100000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "[FLM]  Prefill chunk 1/1 with 50 tokens\nThe number 10 is a fundamental concept in mathematics and has been a cornerstone of human civilization for thousands of years. Let's dive into its concept, etymology, and cultural significance."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Kinetic",
      "uuid": "b1c68983d5ea4d3a9669db19107126ad",
      "x": 14137.134755411014,
      "y": 3496.5395368015766,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.91000000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "**Concept of 10**"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Unfold",
      "uuid": "f3f6bc72ced8441bbb1d1534abf03f5d",
      "x": 14486.726086671382,
      "y": 3530.5128064634555,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 206.0,
      "z_value": -9.90900000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "In mathematics, 10 is the smallest number that is greater than 1 and has a multiplicative inverse (1/10). It is also the first number that can be represented in a decimal system, which is the basis of our modern numerical system. The decimal system is based on the concept of the number 10, where we group numbers into sets of 10 (tens) to make calculations easier."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Unfold",
      "uuid": "d56993351fbd4497875294a09f8ecace",
      "x": 14565.162535337764,
      "y": 3240.340074213638,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.908000000000051,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "**Etymology of 10**"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Fresh Start",
      "uuid": "f0e41ebf7b354d3494935b4f0cc7dff8",
      "x": 15547.857480034963,
      "y": 3514.5772794298596,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 191.0,
      "z_value": -9.904000000000053,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "In modern times, the number 10 has become a cultural icon, with the phrase \"10\" being used in various contexts, such as \"10\" in sports (e.g., the number of players on the field in some games), \"10\" in music (e.g., the \"10th\" note in music theory), and \"10\" in technology (e.g., the \"10th\" anniversary of a company or a product)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Soft",
      "uuid": "0a6d51a6b9ef461eaff71c68b46b85b9",
      "x": 14975.163294199767,
      "y": 3222.180932250072,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 221.0,
      "z_value": -9.907000000000052,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The number 10 has a rich etymology. The word \"ten\" comes from the Latin word \"decem,\" which is derived from the Greek word \"deka,\" meaning \"ten.\" The Greek word \"deka\" is thought to be derived from the Proto-Indo-European word \"*dek-\", which also meant \"ten.\" The Proto-Indo-European language was spoken around 4000 BCE, and it is believed to be the ancestor of many modern languages, including Latin, Greek, and many others."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Delicate",
      "uuid": "515801b1337d4e3a9f6705338f950bda",
      "x": 15341.628182469172,
      "y": 3263.7302226145534,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 206.0,
      "z_value": -9.905000000000053,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The number 10 has been considered sacred or symbolic in many cultures throughout history. In ancient Egypt, the number 10 was considered a sacred number, as it represented the number of gods in the pantheon. In many African cultures, the number 10 is associated with completeness or wholeness, as it represents the idea of a perfect set or a complete cycle."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Pure Light",
      "uuid": "5b22f13a7bd74a7d81af371f89c1e8ed",
      "x": 14848.12665205316,
      "y": 3543.052126254741,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.906000000000052,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "**Cultural Significance of 10**"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Sweet",
      "uuid": "8ff7a1bc57a84ad1b89f1eca0820c840",
      "x": 15297.411341974926,
      "y": 3788.6341698848746,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.903000000000054,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "**Interesting Facts about 10**"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "All Glory",
      "uuid": "45ade9bfc844473b87b3abcce24bdcd5",
      "x": 16155.63889164852,
      "y": 3553.966299201777,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 116.0,
      "z_value": -9.902000000000054,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Here are a few interesting facts about the number 10:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Sweet",
      "uuid": "96a5eab42bfd427da54578f287275116",
      "x": 16084.852719630591,
      "y": 3706.5422072771885,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 236.0,
      "z_value": -9.901000000000055,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "* The number 10 is a factor of many other numbers, such as 20, 30, and 40.\n* The number 10 has a unique property in mathematics, known as the \"10-identity,\" which states that the sum of the numbers from 1 to 10 is equal to 55 (1 + 2 + 3 + ... + 9 + 10 = 55).\n* The number 10 is the first number that can be represented using a decimal system, which is why it is often considered the \"beginning\" of our modern numerical system."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Gentle",
      "uuid": "1537708ab87e486495dafc20e8edc6a1",
      "x": 17370.33661435916,
      "y": 4495.146226784395,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 206.0,
      "z_value": -9.898000000000057,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "In mathematics, 10 is the smallest number that is greater than 1 and has a multiplicative inverse (1/10). It is also the first number that can be represented in a decimal system, which is the basis of our modern numerical system. The decimal system is based on the concept of the number 10, where we group numbers into sets of 10 (tens) to make calculations easier."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Onward",
