      "z_value": -9.991000000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "[FLM]  Prefill chunk 1/1 with 61 tokens\nFLM (Filmora) is a popular video editing software that's known for its user-friendly interface and advanced features. Here's an overview to help you get started:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Irresistible",
      "uuid": "283e49dc719d4205a1a7d8218672e22f",
      "x": 199.3080490011595,
      "y": 391.5138346472372,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.990000000000006,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "**Getting Familiar with FLM Interface**"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Kinetic",
      "uuid": "21188372d5254f168eb3ae50a71b76e0",
      "x": -283.08261435467455,
      "y": 384.77405779670323,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 266.0,
      "z_value": -9.989000000000006,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1. **Home Screen**: The home screen displays the project timeline, where you can drag and drop media files, transitions, and effects.\n2. **Media Library**: The media library is where you store and manage your media files. You can add files, folders, and even import external media sources.\n3. **Project Panel**: The project panel is where you can view and edit your project's settings, such as resolution, frame rate, and audio settings.\n4. **Preview Panel**: The preview panel displays a live preview of your project, allowing you to see how the edits look before applying them."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Delicate",
      "uuid": "44ba834ce08849f2864489086c5210f2",
      "x": 734.9789825496928,
      "y": 389.40225062031413,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 281.0,
      "z_value": -9.985000000000008,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1. **Transitions**: FLM offers a wide range of transitions that can be applied to clips. You can browse and add transitions to your project.\n2. **Effects**: FLM has a variety of effects, such as color adjustments, text overlays, and audio adjustments.\n3. **Timeline Editing**: Use the timeline to trim, split, or merge clips. You can also adjust the duration and timing of clips.\n4. **Keyframe Animation**: Use keyframes to create animations and effects. This involves setting a starting and ending point for an animation and adjusting the values in between."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Clear Vision",
      "uuid": "bd2b9e8d8c8c45a09b2085c061a51037",
      "x": 13.54189097169727,
      "y": 206.95244492622209,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.988000000000007,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "**Basic Editing Techniques**"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Accurate",
      "uuid": "ca5409dcd4bf4c79b9d81c42edd751da",
      "x": 430.8483213116253,
      "y": 242.8152079947723,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.986000000000008,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "**Advanced Editing Features**"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Golden Hour",
      "uuid": "305289de20934961b79d5f0c08e3f4a2",
      "x": -4.452366008532735,
      "y": -127.30239726790302,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 266.0,
      "z_value": -9.987000000000007,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1. **Cut**: To cut a clip, select it and press the 'Cut' button or use the 'Edit' tab.\n2. **Split**: To split a clip, select it and press the 'Split' button or use the 'Edit' tab.\n3. **Merge**: To merge two clips, select them and press the 'Merge' button or use the 'Edit' tab.\n4. **Drag and Drop**: To add a transition or effect, drag it from the media library and drop it onto the timeline.\n5. **Undo and Redo**: Use the 'Undo' and 'Redo' buttons or press Ctrl + Z and Ctrl + Y to switch between these actions."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Infinite Wisdom",
      "uuid": "405f91ed19c34ab1b719a3a66e26c15a",
      "x": 1318.4646996033562,
      "y": 786.7561504964465,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 251.0,
      "z_value": -9.98300000000001,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1. **Start with a Simple Project**: Begin with a simple project, such as a single clip, and experiment with basic editing techniques.\n2. **Use the Preview Panel**: Use the preview panel to see how your edits look before applying them.\n3. **Experiment with Transitions and Effects**: Experiment with different transitions and effects to add visual interest to your project.\n4. **Watch Tutorials**: Watch tutorials and online guides to learn more about FLM's advanced features and techniques."
    },
